The paper deals with a problem in software requirement engineering, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of approximate algorithms and fitness landscape analysis suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The multilevel approach and exploration of search spaces suggest that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The use of performance metrics and experimental results suggest that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the NP-hard nature of the problem suggests that it may belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category.
